The new Osun State Commissioner of Police, CP Julius Okoro said he has put stringent security mechanisms to ensure the peaceful celebration of this year’s Eid-El Kabir. The Police boss assured the people of the state that the Police Command will continue to work assiduously to guarantee the safety of lives and property of the entire citizenry before, during and beyond the festival. This is contained in a statement signed by that Command’s Police Public Relations Officer, SP Yemisi Opalola on Friday. Okoro said the Command will continue to perform its statutory duty of protection of lives and property and is ever ready, more determined to ensure conducive and peaceful co-existence among the citizenry. The statement read, ‘’To this end, the State Police Command urged the people of the State to conduct themselves within the ambits of the law and go about their lawful duties. They are to report any suspicious movement to the Police and voluntarily give prompt and useful information in case of any infraction of the law through these numbers: 08067788119, 08039537995, 08123823981 and 08075872433.’’